Ensures these systems are in compliance with task or specifications and government requirements. Provides direction and supervision to other management and technical staff.

raw_data.title: On-Site Systems Administrator
raw_data.description: This resource is located at the customer site and provides daily support and system troubleshooting of the entire production system software, inclusive of custom software application services. The trained, experienced on-site systems administrator will perform expert-level systems management and configuration. This person provides systems administration services, in-house support services for system users, system application development services, migration services if required, and problem escalation of both platform software and custom application incidents to the customer Help Desk for assistance. The on-site systems administrator is familiar with the customer’s specific technical configuration and environment.
